/wiki/Fair_City: Fair City is an Irish television soap opera which has been broadcast on RTÉ One since 1989. Produced by the public service broadcaster Raidió Teilifís Éireann (RTÉ), it first aired on Monday 18 September 1989. It has won several awards and is both the most popular and the longest running Irish drama serial.
/wiki/Tom_Jordan_(actor): Tom Jordan (1937 – 29 June 2019) was an Irish actor best known for his part as Charlie Kelly in the Irish soap opera Fair City, a part he had for thirty years between the start of the series in 1989 and his death in 2019.
/wiki/Jim_Bartley_(actor): Jim Bartley (born 1945) is an Irish actor best known for his part as Bela Doyle in the Irish soap opera Fair City, a part he has had since 1990.His other television credits include Fatal Inheritance, The Bill, Joyriders, Taffin, The Fantasist, Inside, The Irish R.M., Teems of Times, Coronation Street, Underground, Ulysses, Tolka Row and Z-Cars. He has also had film roles in War of the Buttons, M.A.N.: Matrix Adjusted Normal, Teresa's Wedding and The Pink Panther Strikes Again.
/wiki/Martina_Stanley: Martina Stanley is an Irish actress known primarily for her acting work in soap opera Fair City. She plays Dolores Molloy, a former hairdresser who lives in Carrigstown.

/wiki/Suzanne_Halpin: Suzanne Halpin (née Doyle) is a fictional character in the Irish soap opera Fair City. The character is portrayed by Sarah Flood. She was first seen on-screen during the opening episode in 1989.

/wiki/Ros_na_R\u00fan: Ros na Rún is an Irish soap opera produced for the Irish-language television channel TG4. The series is set in a fictional village called Ros Na Rún, located near to An Spidéal, and focuses on the domestic and professional lives of its residents.
/wiki/Fionnuala_N\u00ed_Fhlatharta: Fionnuala Ní Fhlatharta is an Irish actress. She is best known for her role as Bernie in the Irish language television drama Ros na Rún.

/wiki/M\u00e1ire_U\u00ed_Dhroighne\u00e1: Máire Uí Dhroigneáin is an Irish actress and sean-nós singer. She is a native of Spiddal, County Galway, Ireland.

/wiki/Barry_O'Hanlon: Barry O'Hanlon is a fictional character in the Irish soap opera Fair City, portrayed by Pat Nolan. One of the show's original characters, Barry first appears in 1989. Barry is usually a nice guy but a little bit downtrodden. He has been summarised as "the unlucky in love ex-teacher who now runs the local paper and used to be involved with Niamh before Paul swept her off her feet (that's only the half of it)".

/wiki/Joe_Steve_\u00d3_Neachtain: Joe Steve Ó Neachtain (1942–2020) was an Irish writer, actor, playwright and broadcaster in the Irish language. He was well known for his portrayal of Peadar Ó Conghaile in the long-running soap Ros na Rún. Ó Neachtain, a native speaker of Irish, was born in An Spidéal, County Galway.
/wiki/List_of_longest-serving_soap_opera: This is a list of longest-serving soap opera actors from radio and television soap operas, as well as the longest-serving performers by country. The list details actors with ten or more years spent on one soap opera, despite itinerant breaks in some cases with the actor/actress portraying multiple roles.
